claim.claim-text:
6. A process for producing a magnetic tape cassette having a base with an opening for forming a transparent window and a window member to be installed in said opening, comprising the steps of: 
molding said window member of a material having no compatibility or having an extremely low degree of compatibility with the material of which said base is made; 
molding said base in such a way that said base has in at least a part of an inner circumferential area of said opening an adequately rigid upper window frame, an elastically deformable lower window frame and a temporary fitting portion that allows said window member to be inserted between said upper and lower window frames, said base and said window member being molded to such that said upper window frame or said lower window frame around said opening in said base or said window member has a projection in a position where said upper window frame or said lower window frame contacts said window member; 
inserting said window member into said temporary fitting portion around said opening in said base so that said lower window frame deforms elastically to achieve temporary joint between said window member and said base; and 
allowing ultrasonic waves or heat to act on said temporary joint.

9. A process for producing a magnetic tape cassette having a base with an opening for forming a transparent window and a transparent resin-made window member to close said opening in said base, comprising the steps of: 
preparing a die assembly for molding said base which has a first sliding member which can be moved from one side of said base in order to form said opening and a second sliding member which can be moved from the other side of said base and which has at both ends recesses for providing said opening with ridges that engage said window member; 
bringing said first sliding member into intimate contact with said second sliding member; 
injecting a base forming material to mold said base having said opening; 
causing said first sliding member and said second sliding member to be spaced apart; and 
injecting into a resulting space a window member forming material that has no compatibility or has an extremely low degree of compatibility with said base forming material, whereby said window member is molded as an integral part of said base.
